sveltejs/svelte#17678.body:
### Describe the bug

With Svelte 5, The `{#await promise}` block does not switch the content if the variable `promise` is resolved or rejected in the same cycle, like `promise = Promise.resolve()`. It works with Svelte 4

It works if you assign a new promise that is fulfilled over:

- `setTimeout()`
- `requestAnimationFrame()`
- `fetch()`
- `tick()` (Svelte)

But:

- `Promise.resolve()`
- [`queueMicrotask()`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTML_DOM_API/Microtask_guide)

Assigning a new fulfilled promise instance is useful when it withdraws data from cache: `p = cache ? Promise.resolve(cache) : fetch(...)`

### Reproduction

```svelte
<script>
	let p = null;
</script>

<button on:click={()=>{
	p = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
		resolve(); // not works
	});
}}>Resolve (immediate)</button>
<button on:click={()=>{
	p = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
		setTimeout(() => resolve(), 1); // works
	});
}}>Resolve (timeout)</button>

<p>
	{#await p}
		...
	{:then v}
		resolved [{v}]
	{:catch err}
		err [{err}]
	{/await}
</p>
```

