- [Remote function documentation](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/remote-functions) uses `kit` and `compilerOptions` keys
- New template uses the `vitePlugin` key

This is the merged result:

```js
/** @type {import('@sveltejs/kit').Config} */
const config = {
  kit: {
    experimental: { remoteFunctions: true },
    adapter: adapter(),
  },
  compilerOptions: {
    experimental: { async: true },
  },
  vitePlugin: {
    dynamicCompileOptions: ({ filename }) => ({ runes: !filename.includes('node_modules') }),
  },
};
```

Could the `dynamicCompileOptions` be moved into `compilerOptions` since it is related to runes only?

Or the other way around and update the documentation:

```js
